{"questionId":"9667","questionHtml":"<p>Hence, state, with a reason, what can be deduced about the values of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"p\">\n  <mi>p</mi>\n</math></span>, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"q\">\n  <mi>q</mi>\n</math></span>, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"r\">\n  <mi>r</mi>\n</math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>The last minimal edge chosen must connect to E , so since <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"s = 8\">\n  <mi>s</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>8</mn>\n</math></span> each of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"p\">\n  <mi>p</mi>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"q\">\n  <mi>q</mi>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"r\">\n  <mi>r</mi>\n</math></span> must be&nbsp;≥ 9.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>R1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9667","referenceCode":"EXM.1.AHL.TZ0.1c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Hence, state, with a reason, what can be deduced about the values of p , q , r .","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.16—Tree and cycle algorithms, Chinese postman, travelling salesman"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}